<subSubSection id="369CC49706AE8A7D5919038B58F4BCA4" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="notes">
<paragraph id="799BAC21BD05E5B8135BFB97DAFD4E70" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F2408B88EEC72B6A6B60E2A38C5B6182" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
The characteristics of the holotype specimen 
<taxonomicName id="935441C6B46B1EE3C34C054A9C96BF13" authorityName="Q. R Li &amp; J. C. Kang" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Lin &amp; Samarakoon &amp; Hyde &amp; Shen &amp; Liao &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Long &amp; Kang &amp; Kang" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila miscanthi" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis id="938989A8DE30F00BDB26F90253D3DEB0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(≡ 
<taxonomicName id="D14EAE768246658E090C40EF2DA9C7D4" authority="Karun., C.H.Kuo &amp; K.D.Hyde, 2020" authorityName="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Lin &amp; Samarakoon &amp; Hyde &amp; Shen &amp; Liao &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Long &amp; Kang &amp; Kang" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Lin &amp; Samarakoon &amp; Hyde &amp; Shen &amp; Liao &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Long &amp; Kang &amp; Kang" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Alishanica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alishanica miscanthi" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis id="F8CED6D37F462475EF67645EE3D5E95B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Alishanica miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) were revised, re-measured and described. 
<taxonomicName id="C1289659B4713C2864354C0A1D56D5BB" authority="Karun., C.H.Kuo &amp; K.D.Hyde, 2020" authorityName="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Lin &amp; Samarakoon &amp; Hyde &amp; Shen &amp; Liao &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Long &amp; Kang &amp; Kang" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Lin &amp; Samarakoon &amp; Hyde &amp; Shen &amp; Liao &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Long &amp; Kang &amp; Kang" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Alishanica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alishanica miscanthi" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis id="61D99A7DF5AE13BF57ABCDB18C3E5774" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Alishanica miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="CB8A210AE2E70356C109A600260FA567" genus="A." lsidName="A. muroiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="muroiana">
<emphasis id="DF21ABA24CCFFCFE1C98706D2D01C024" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. muroiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F8ECABA5BBFCA2DF40131146C5498E06" genus="A." lsidName="A. serrulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="serrulata">
<emphasis id="131F15612A2965A52949A252B58ADABF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. serrulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="34D6F458E8B16773B3F5EC5F63318146" author="Wang, YZ" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity Research Series" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" pagination="1 - 168" refId="B59" refString="Wang, YZ, Aptroot, A, Hyde, KD, 2004. Revision of the genus Amphisphaeria. Hong Kong SAR, China. Fungal Diversity Research Series 13: 1 - 168" title="Revision of the genus Amphisphaeria. Hong Kong SAR, China." volume="13" year="2004">Wang et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="0253376477F4EAD75105119A16258B23" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B20" refString="Hyde, KD, Norphanphoun, C, Maharachchikumbura, SSN, Bhat, DJ, Jones, EBG, Bundhun, D, Chen, YJ, Bao, DF, Boonmee, S, Calabon, MS, 2020. Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11(1): 305-1059. https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" title="Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11 (1): 305 - 1059." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" year="2020">Hyde et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). However, no clypeus was observed for 
<taxonomicName id="98D932C702FE953B71342E6796F5AB0B" genus="A." lsidName="A. muroiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="muroiana">
<emphasis id="3F23A7C1D76E8EBF33DE41BF6DAAB1DD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. muroiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="F16A9C2B086622DF21560FD0D922ACD7" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila serrulata" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="serrulata">
<emphasis id="49C54D8BBE48432B11DC776B8D5A0EBE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila serrulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has larger ascomata (480-560 
<normalizedToken id="FAB301D2BBBD9968F9A5A12706EFC78D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
280-320 
<normalizedToken id="0CCA74C5C8EA2CBCBA224EE24E5D80DB" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) with a central papilla surrounded by a circle of white tissue (
<bibRefCitation id="A9E38CF8F2A88E19F9E9718BDE8286CE" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B19" refString="Hyde, KD, 1996. Fungi from palms. XXIX. Arecophila gen. nov. (Amphisphaeriaceae, Ascomycota), with five new species and two new combinations. Nova Hedwigia 63(1/2): 81-100." title="Fungi from palms. XXIX. Arecophila gen. nov. (Amphisphaeriaceae, Ascomycota), with five new species and two new combinations. Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 / 2): 81 - 100." year="1996">Hyde 1996</bibRefCitation>
) which differs from those of 
<taxonomicName id="B7046974B422C5B39DC24EE5FC82EA28" genus="A." lsidName="A. miscanthi" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis id="83B57B0C31D41BC0077BE0FD64E6B8D4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. One new collection (GZUH0122, Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B3A1E833C6D2CFD6F810D1650CF8B795" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Arecophila miscanthi (GZUH 0122) A, B ascomata on the surface of host C paraphyses and asci D section of ascoma E peridium F, G apical rings H-K asci with ascospores M-P ascospores. Scale bars: 50 μm (C, D); 10 μm (E, F-K); 5 μm (L-P)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.88.79475.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672051" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">5</figureCitation>
) shows the same traits of 
<taxonomicName id="F6C60FBBE10B6815EA255E0122D253F4" genus="A." lsidName="A. miscanthi" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis id="A012748F25D4C247E29DD6FB7C222B27" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MFLU 19-2333) in having immersed ascomata with clypeus, a wedge-shaped J+, ascus subapical ring, same dimensions of ascospores and here we provide it as a new geographical record from China.
</paragraph>
<caption id="4A633773EA874534DABC269DDCC7C057" doi="10.3897/mycokeys.88.79475.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/672051" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
